review_blob: Pours a light gold with a thin white head. Aroma of sour wheat, oak and funk. Taste is sour, fruity, earthy with a dry oaky finish.
Pours a light gold. Aroma of wheat, oak and funk. Taste follows but with cardboard and an off putting stale candy note. Not loving this one.
Pours a golden orange with a thick white head. Aroma of big citrus and grain. Taste is a citrusy bomb. Nice bitterness
Pours alight gold with a thin white head. Aroma big on citrus and malt with a hint of alcohol. Taste with sweet and malty with a big citrus bite. Nice balance. Easy to drink for a dipa
beer_name: Only Child Dont Tell Mom The Baby Citras Dead

review_blob: Pours a gold with a thin white head. Aroma of sour wheat and hops. Taste follows. Do they just use one base sour wheat at Westbrook? This beer tastes like nomader with hops or Westbrook Gose with hops and no spice. Nonetheless this is a great session hoppy sour
beer_name: Evil Twin / Intangible Ales Sour Bikini

review_blob: Pours brown with a light tan head. Aroma of malt and English hops. Taste is light malt, mild hops and a hint of bourbon. Light and easy to drink with a hint of barrel.

Wow, thats really all I can say. Well not all because I dont give crappy rates like fluffy. Pours jet black with a thick mocha head. Aroma of coconut, bourbon, milk chocolate and maple. Taste follows, sweet maple bourbon, molasses, coconut and milk chocolate. Sweet and chewy. This is a dessert beer that I wish I could have all the time. This is simply amazing, I am out of words to explain how amazing this beer is.
Pours a golden orange with a thick white head. Aroma of big peach with ginger and wheat. Very nice
beer_name: Saucony Creek xReserve 05-15: Peach & Ginger Saison

review_blob: Pours jet black with a thick mocha head. Aroma of maple syrup and pecan pie. Taste follows, thick and chewy. Dessert in a glass
pours a light golden orange with a thin white head. Aroma of tropical fruit and pine. Taste is freshly milled grain, passion fruit and pine. crisp and juicy

Pours a muddy dark brown with a thick mocha head. Aroma of raspberries and hops. Taste is like a chocolate covered raspberry. Creamy, slightly sweet, chocolate and jam with a hoppy finish. I had my doubts about this one but I love it!
beer_name: Tired Hands / Omnipollo Milkshake IPA - Chocolate & Raspberry

review_blob: Pours jet black with a thick mocha head. Aroma of roast and bitter pine. Taste is roast, dark chocolate and pine.
Pours a light yellow with a thick white head. Aroma of caramel and orange peel. Taste is like an orange creamsickle. Light yet with a really cool flavor.
Pours a hazy gold with a thick white head. Aroma of grass, earth, white grapes. Taste follows, loads of white grape juice, sweet and earthy
Pours a light yellow with a thick white head. Aroma of orange juice, grain and passion fruit. Taste is bitter citrus, grain and tropical fruit. Very crisp.
Pours a light gold. Aroma of honey, bourbon and vanilla. Taste is honey, bourbon and vanilla. Viscous yet smooth and silky. Very nice.
Pours a dark purple with a thin pink head. Aroma of gin, oak and berries. Taste is sour wheat, oak, funk, gin and berries. Tastes like a cocktail
Pours a deep purple with no head. Aroma of raspberries, grape jelly, oak and sour wheat. Taste is sour wheat, berries, jam, oak and funk. So much berry presence.
Pours a bright (yet hazy) golden orange with no head. Aroma of oak, funk and stone fruit. Taste follows, very sour, wheat, oak, funk and stone fruit.
Pours a reddish orange with a thick offwhite head. Aroma of berries, malt, and orange juice. Taste is oranges, berries, green pepper and tropical fruit.
Pours a hazy yellow with a thick white head. Aroma of grain, pepper, stone fruit and tropical fruit. Taste is earthy grain, pears, pepper and tropical fruit.
beer_name: Tired Hands Eventually We All Just Fade Into The Grey Oblivion

review_blob: Pours a light Amber with a thin white head. Aroma of bread, caramel and grain. Taste is malty, bready, slightly sweet but finishes slightly dry. Very nice.
Pours jet black with a thin mocha head. Aroma of bourbon, oak, vanilla and coffee. Taste follows, smooth with a nice dose of chocolate. Medium body with a ton of flavor, great barrel presence
Pours a thin black with a thick mocha head. Aroma of milk chocolate, roast, vanilla. Taste follows with peppers in the finish with a hint of bourbon and oak. Very nice but a bit thin
Pours a hazy orange with a thick white head. Aroma of wheat, citrus and lacto. Taste is sour wheat, citrus and spices. Light and crisp with a lot of flavor.
Pours a bright reddish purple with a thick pink head. Aroma of blueberries, vanilla, and grain. Taste is tart, blueberries, grain, vanilla and lactose. Very different in a good way
Pours a light translucent yellow with a thick white head. Aroma of grain, citrus and earth. Taste is freshly milled grain, bread, grapefruit and grass. Really crisp and bright.
beer_name: Tired Hands Dry Hopped Trendler Pilsner

review_blob: Pours a hazy gold with a thick white head. Aroma of oak, funk, citrus and malt. Taste follows with some tart lemon zest notes. Very nice.
Pours jet black with a thick brown head. Aroma of milk chocolate, vanilla, and molasses. Taste follows with a cinnamon crunch note. Really tasty stout.
Pours a hazy gold, a lot of particulate and a thin white head. Aroma of sweet malt, honey, grass and earth. Taste is sweet malt, herbal and grassy. A bit too sweet for my liking.

Pours a hazy bright orange with a thick white head. Aroma of funk, oak, citrus and bitter hops. Taste is big Belgian funk, bitter citrus, oak and pine with a dry vinous finish. Plain and simple this is one of the best non-sour saisons that I have ever had. Forest and main is killing it!
Pours a deep reddish purple with a thin pink head. Aroma of berries, oak and vinous notes. Taste is sour, acidic, with berries and oak. Not bad but very sour, hard to drink a lot.
Pours gold with a thin white head. Aroma of grapefruit and bitter hops. Taste follows, grapefruit is present but seems artificial.

Pours a golden orange with a thick white head. Aroma of passion fruit, oak and sour wheat. Taste follows, sour wheat and passion fruit with an oaky finish. This is fantastic, very sour with loads of passion fruit
Pours a hazy golden orange with a thin white head. Aroma of ginger, oak and lacto. Taste is sour wheat, oak, funk and ginger. Very nice.
Nitro pour. Black with a cascading mocha head. Aroma big on bitter roast. Taste follows, like a very roast forward Guinness.
Pours a reddish orange with a thin white head. Aroma of tropical fruit and bitter citrusy hops. Taste follows, hard to distinguish the fruit and ginger in the taste but its a decent IPA
Pours gold with a thin white head. Aroma of malt and banana esters. Taste follows, with a big punch of alcohol. I couldnt finish the can.
beer_name: Round Guys Sanctified Belgian Golden Strong

review_blob: Pours black with a thick offwhite head. Aroma of peanut butter, roast and cardboard. Taste follows, peanut butter is there but there is an unpleasant cardboard taste that is off putting.
Pours jet black with a thin mocha head. Aroma of roast and bitter pine. Taste is roast, dark chocolate and bitter piney hops. Really nice even for a style that I dont typically enjoy
beer_name: Cigar City / Three Floyds Florida Man Loses Bet

review_blob: Pours jet black with a thin mocha head. Aroma of milk chocolate, roast and vanilla. Taste is chocolate and vanilla with a touch of roast. Smooth and creamy porter
beer_name: Saucony Creek xReserve: Imperial Vanilla Porter

review_blob: Pours jet black with a thin off white head. Aroma of bakers chocolate, roast and coffee. Taste follows, chocolate and coffee. Really solid.
beer_name: Saucony Creek xReserve 04-14: Imperial Coffee Stout

review_blob: Pours a reddish orange with a thick white head. Aroma of tropical fruit, citrus and punch. Taste follows, like a hoppy fruit punch. Wow this is fantastic

Pours a translucent yellow with a thick white head. Aroma of bitter old school hops and biscuit. Taste is clean, crisp, slightly bitter with a biscuitty finish. This is by far the most true to style American take on a helles. They need to can this
Pours jet black with a thick mocha head. Aroma of roast and bakers chocolate. Taste is blueberries up front with roast and alcohol burn.
Pours jet black with a mocha head. Aroma of tart cherries and roast. Taste follows, smoke and cherries. A bit light for a porter but it tastes great.
Pours a hazy light yellow with a thick white head. Aroma of oak, funk and lemon. Taste is wheat, oak, funk and citrus with an herbal finish. Very nice.
Pours a hazy gold with a thick white head. Aroma of citrus, malt and earth. Taste is bitter citrus with a medicinal note, sweet and malty.
Pours a hazy yellow with a thick white head. Aroma of earth, grass, grain and pine. Taste follows, sweet with bitter pine.
Pours a bright gold, aroma of apple pie, apple juice and spices. Taste is honey, brown sugar, Apple juice and cloves. Very nice, sweet mead.
